  "body": "Right now the only way to test different base fees is to have a base fee getter method in your contract, then have a dedicated test contract that lets you override the base fee.\r\n\r\nA cheatcode can remove the need for this, and should behave similarly to `warp` and `roll` in that it's persistent until called again\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\ninterface Vm {\r\n  // Set block.basefee (newBasefee)\r\n  function fee(uint256) external;\r\n}\r\n```",
